article.headline: Saint Bonaventure defeats UMass 75-67
article.description: — Chad Venning had 16 points in Saint Bonaventure's 75-67 victory against UMass on Saturday.
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. -- — Chad Venning had 16 points in Saint Bonaventure's 75-67 victory against UMass on Saturday. Venning added 10 rebounds for the Bonnies (17-10, 8-7 Atlantic 10 Conference). Moses Flowers scored 15 points and added five rebounds. Mika Adams-Woods was 5 of 14 shooting, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 2 for 3 from the line to finish with 14 points. Josh Cohen led the way for the Minutemen (17-10, 8-7) with 18 points and six rebounds. Rahsool Diggins added 12 points for UMass. In addition, Jaylen Curry had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
